name: PAINTING
description:
Title: Et Aint
Year: 2001
Artist: Tracy McCormick
Material: Acrylic and Elmer's glue on canvas
Overall dimensions: 

This painting combines a mild riff on Rene Magritte's "Ceci n'est pas une pipe" with a little dash of southern grammar and a bit of a Picasso-type guitar obsession.

The guitar was an image torn from an old classified ad.  I simply wanted to paint it and once I saw a "wet paint" sign I had my reason.

Between the guitar and the wet paint sign I couldn't help but think of Magritte.  

Clearly the wet paint sign was not wet nor was it paint.  I couldn't help but see "et aint" and find humor in the fact that using incorrect grammar could get you to the real Magritte-type truth of the sign.

The text "et aint" is superimposed on top of the guitar using Elmer's glue.  The glue helps give it a "wet look" and helps to address the notion of attaching meaning to arbitrary sounds and characters.

name: FILE CABINET
description:
